 "cells": [
  {

   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Estimate Step Complexity"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "2dcbf04a",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The simulator allows to compare Kleinberg's original bounds with simulation and to conjecture tighter bounds."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "id": "6e246b32",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from kleinberg_grid_simulator import estimate_alpha, parallelize\n",
    "from matplotlib import pyplot as plt"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "id": "913cc4a6",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stderr",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "100%|███████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████| 41/41 [00:00<00:00, 95.43it/s]\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "rr = [r/10 for r in range(0, 41)]\n",
    "res = parallelize([{'r': r, 'budget': 10000 if r!=2 else 1000} for r in rr], function=estimate_alpha)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "id": "f9bc6e01",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 640x480 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "plt.plot(rr, [re[0] for re in res], marker='o', markersize=2, label='Simulation')\n",
    "plt.plot(rr, [(2-r)/(3-r) if r<2 else ( r-2 if r<3 else 1 ) for r in rr], '--', label=\"Conjectured bounds\")\n",
    "plt.plot(rr, [(2-r)/3 if r<2 else (r-2)/(r-1) for r in rr], '-.', label=\"Kleinberg's original bounds\")\n",
    "plt.legend()\n",
    "plt.xlim([0, 4])\n",
    "plt.xlabel('$r$')\n",
    "plt.ylabel('$\\\\alpha$')\n",
    "plt.ylim([0, 1.1])\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "911ac943",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Look how far we went to compute the values:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "id": "87198a13",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 640x480 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "plt.semilogy(rr, [re[1] for re in res])\n",
    "plt.xlim([0, 4])\n",
    "plt.xlabel('$r$')\n",
    "plt.ylabel('Max value of $n$ considered')\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  }
 ],
